  "prompt": "Are there any good spatial econometrics classes at Harvard or MIT?",
  "response": "As of the most recent information, both Harvard University and the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) offer courses in econometrics and related fields, but the availability of specific courses in spatial econometrics can vary by semester and department. Here are some options and resources to consider:\n\n### Harvard University\n\n1. **Economics Department**:\n   - **Econometrics Courses**: Harvard\u2019s Economics Department offers several courses in econometrics, which may include topics in spatial econometrics as part of broader econometric methods.\n   - **Advanced Topics**: Look for advanced econometrics courses or seminars that might cover spatial econometrics. Courses like \"Econometric Theory\" or \"Applied Econometrics\" sometimes include spatial topics.\n\n2. **Harvard Kennedy School**:\n   - **Public Policy and Urban Planning**: Courses in urban economics, public policy, and regional planning might touch on spatial econometrics. Check courses in the Harvard Kennedy School or the Department of Urban Planning and Design.\n\n3. **Harvard University Extension School**:\n   - **Online and Part-Time Courses**: The Extension School sometimes offers courses in econometrics and related fields that may include spatial econometrics.\n\n### Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)\n\n1. **Economics Department**:\n   - **Econometrics Courses**: MIT offers robust econometrics training through its Economics Department. Courses like \"Econometrics\" and \"Advanced Econometrics\" may cover spatial econometrics as part of the curriculum.\n   - **Research Seminars**: Graduate research seminars often delve into specialized topics, including spatial econometrics.\n\n2. **Urban Studies and Planning (DUSP)**:\n   - **Urban Economics and Planning**: MIT\u2019s Department of Urban Studies and Planning offers courses in urban economics, regional science, and spatial analysis, which may include spatial econometrics.\n\n3. **Sloan School of Management**:\n   - **Applied Economics and Management**: Courses in applied economics and management at Sloan may also cover spatial econometrics, particularly in the context of regional and urban economics.\n\n### Cross-Registration and Resources\n\n- **Cross-Registration**: Students at Harvard and MIT can cross-register for courses at each other\u2019s institutions, expanding access to specialized courses.\n- **Workshops and Seminars**: Both universities host workshops, seminars, and guest lectures that may cover spatial econometrics. Regularly check departmental announcements and event calendars.\n- **Online Resources**: Explore online course offerings and resources through platforms like MIT OpenCourseWare and Harvard Online Learning for additional materials on spatial econometrics.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- **Course Catalogs**: Review the latest course catalogs and syllabi for detailed information on course content.\n- **Faculty Advisors**: Consult with faculty advisors or professors in the economics, urban planning, or related departments for specific course recommendations.\n- **Academic Journals and Conferences**: Engage with academic journals and conferences in spatial econometrics to stay updated on the latest research and educational opportunities.\n\nFor the most accurate and current information, directly access the course listings and contact departments at Harvard and MIT.",
